# Page Audit Report - AccreditEx Application

**Date:** December 2, 2025  
**Total Pages Audited:** 32 pages  
**Report Type:** Functional Overlap & Merge Opportunity Analysis

---

## Executive Summary

After comprehensive analysis of all 32 pages in the application, **4 HIGH-PRIORITY merge opportunities** have been identified that can improve UX/UI without impacting functionality:

1. **DocumentsPage â†” DocumentControlHubPage** - Duplicate document management
2. **AuditHubPage â†” AuditLogPage** - Related audit functionality spread across pages
3. **ProjectListPage â†” ProjectDetailPage** - List/detail separation (consider unified interface)
4. **TrainingDetailPage â†” TrainingHubPage** - Training management scattered

---

## Page Categories & Functional Groups

### 1. **List/Detail Pages** (Core Content Management)
- ProjectListPage â† â†’ ProjectDetailPage
- TrainingHubPage â† â†’ TrainingDetailPage
- DepartmentsPage â† â†’ DepartmentDetailPage
- AccreditationHubPage (no detail view - redirects to StandardsPage)

### 2. **Hub/Dashboard Pages** (Multi-tab Interfaces)
- RiskHubPage (4 tabs: register, capa, incidents, checks)
- TrainingHubPage (2 tabs: myTraining, admin)
- DocumentControlHubPage (3 categories: all, my_documents, recent)
- DataHubPage (statistics + export/import)

### 3. **Standalone Pages** (No Related Pages)
- DashboardPage (main entry)
- LoginPage (authentication)
- OnboardingPage (new users)
- AnalyticsPage (analytics dashboard)
- QualityInsightsPage (insights dashboard)
- CalendarPage (calendar view)
- MyTasksPage (task management)
- UserProfilePage (user profile detail)
- CertificatePage (certificate viewer)
- CreateProjectPage (project creation flow)
- ProjectOverview (project overview - used in ProjectDetailPage)
- DesignControlsPage (design controls - used in ProjectDetailPage)
- MockSurveyPage (survey - used in ProjectDetailPage)
- MockSurveyListPage (survey list - used in ProjectDetailPage)
- MessagingPage (messaging system)
- UsersPage (user management)
- DocumentsPage (DEPRECATED - placeholder)

